44
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:24,290
His Majesty has died. We cannot delay even for a while.

45
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:26,240
How did that happen?

46
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:28,760
Reporting to General. His Majesty was assassinated.

47
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,580
Second Prince has retreated after hearing about the news.

48
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:33,890
Duke Cheng and Marquis Qinghe have already led the army southward to give support.

49
00:05:33,890 --> 00:05:36,040
General, if we face the battle alone,

50
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:38,870
there's bound to be many tragic deaths, General.

51
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:46,700
General, the nation cannot be governed by no one.

52
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:51,620
I'm afraid if we don't go back, all the princes will kill each other to seize power.

53
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:55,760
Please help me to get back to the capital to preside over the situation.

54
00:06:04,690 --> 00:06:07,440
Withdraw the soldiers.

55
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:15,090
[An Hua Gate]

56
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:54,030
Surrender.

57
00:07:07,210 --> 00:07:09,320
Everybody, listen!

58
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:12,490
I killed your emperor.

59
00:07:12,490 --> 00:07:16,270
Our reinforcement army has surrounded Prince Dapeng's army.

60
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:18,930
Surrender immediately!

61
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:27,730
The capital was guarded successfully?

62
00:09:27,730 --> 00:09:29,800
Yes, Your Majesty.

63
00:09:30,420 --> 00:09:33,840
Really unexpected. Quick tell me! How it was guarded?

64
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:36,310
Zhu Zan killed the Northern Qi's emperor.

65
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:39,400
Additionally, Duke Cheng and Marquis Qinghe led their armies to rush to the rescue.

66
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,570
Northern Qi suffered a crushing defeat.

67
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:53,320
Zhu Shan committed the crime of conspiracy for treason.

68
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:56,700
This matter has long spread everywhere.

69
00:09:56,700 --> 00:10:01,520
But now, he led people to the successful defense of the capital.

70
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:08,180
You tell me... What will my people think?

71
00:10:09,330 --> 00:10:13,210
Your Majesty, the crime of conspiracy for treason was mentioned by Lord Huang.

72
00:10:13,210 --> 00:10:15,690
The evidence was also presented by him.

73
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:18,430
You only trusted Lord Huang, that's all.

74
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:23,340
Furthermore, you also gave Duke Cheng a chance, and summoned him back to explain clearly.

75
00:10:23,340 --> 00:10:27,050
Also, Duke Cheng insisted on not coming back, defying the imperial decree, then fled.

76
00:10:27,050 --> 00:10:30,220
All these misunderstandings led to the current situation.

77
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:32,590
It was also not your responsibility.

78
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:34,510
And now Lord Huang is missing.

79
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:39,550
Maybe he has a guilty conscience, having the chance of leaving the city in disguise.

80
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:42,610
When in fact, he already escaped.

81
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:46,110
Huang Cheng is missing?

82
00:10:46,110 --> 00:10:47,400
Yes.

83
00:10:51,340 --> 00:10:55,180
If what you said is true,

84
00:10:55,710 --> 00:11:00,200
that means I believed some villain's one-sided story

85
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:04,530
and wronged Duke Cheng. What a huge mistake!

86
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:09,590
I left the capital to avoid the war, which everyone knows.

87
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:13,570
Now the capital has survived it.

88
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:18,960
Tell me.

89
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:22,110
How should I go back?

90
00:11:22,110 --> 00:11:25,190
Your Majesty, Physician Jun and Prince Xian explained to the public

91
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:29,160
that before Northern Qi surrounded the city, Your Majesty left to take the blame at the Imperial Mausoleum

92
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:33,490
to apologize to the ancestors for the hard times caused by the war between two nations.

93
00:11:33,490 --> 00:11:38,050
Unexpectedly, before you returned to the capital, Northern Qi had surrounded the city.

94
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:42,180
You couldn't physically go back to the capital, but you've been spiritually with the capital.

95
00:11:42,180 --> 00:11:44,380
Even the assassination carried out by Zhu Zan

96
00:11:44,380 --> 00:11:47,920
and Duke Cheng and Marquis Qinghe's strategy to take the army back and defend the city

97
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:50,220
were Your Majesty's orders.

98
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:54,690
Did they really say that?

99
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:56,170
Yes.

100
00:11:57,590 --> 00:12:01,740
Your Majesty, a nation can't go a day without an emperor. Since the capital is out of trouble,

101
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:05,680
they still need you to go back and take over the reins.

102
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:10,510
Everyone, get the guard of honor ready.

103
00:12:10,510 --> 00:12:13,080
We'll get going early in the morning.

104
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,460
Yes.

105
00:12:14,460 --> 00:12:18,200
Lu Yunqi, stay behind for now.

106
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:23,020
Your Majesty.

107
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:32,990
Tell me why Jun Jiuling did that.

108
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:36,930
I don't know what you mean, Your Majesty.

109
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:44,600
Prince Xian surely said it for my sake.

110
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:48,870
But Jun Jiuling said it.

111
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:51,500
Why?

112
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:55,460
Maybe she wants to beg for mercy for Duke Cheng.

113
00:12:57,270 --> 00:12:59,090
No.

114
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:02,650
I'm starting to find

115
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:06,270
this woman to be not simple at all.

116
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:08,190
She let Prince Huai out.

117
00:13:08,190 --> 00:13:11,570
What Prince Huai said on the streets

118
00:13:12,380 --> 00:13:15,130
such as "I'm with you all."

119
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:17,570
and "Everyone's suffering because the Imperial Court didn't do well"

120
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:20,720
must've been taught by her.

121
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,610
Can't you tell?

122
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:26,810
It obviously alluded to me.

123
00:13:32,690 --> 00:13:37,140
She could incite everyone in the capital

124
00:13:37,140 --> 00:13:39,510
to guard the city with her.

125
00:13:39,510 --> 00:13:45,270
Maybe she'll be able to incite everyone tomorrow

126
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:49,490
to do something else with her.

127
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:56,890
Kill her.

128
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:00,950
Yes, Your Majesty.

129
00:14:27,710 --> 00:14:29,550
Lord Lu,

130
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:41,090
- did His Majesty want to have her killed?
- Yes.

131
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:42,870
- Did you say yes?
- I can't disobey His Majesty's orders.

132
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:45,140
- When are you going to do it?
- You can't help her.

133
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:47,430
What about both of us?

134
00:14:56,930 --> 00:15:01,990
Ning Yunzhao, do you know what you're talking about?

135
00:15:01,990 --> 00:15:04,780
I know very well.

136
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:08,920
Do you want to keep her alive no matter what?

137
00:15:10,260 --> 00:15:13,470
The way you put it isn't wrong.

138
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:16,510
It's just a bit narrow. What I want

139
00:15:16,510 --> 00:15:19,980
is just peaceful times with a sensible emperor and virtuous ministers.

140
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:25,010
I see.

141
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:28,160
Did you hide the Imperial Jade Seal for this reason?

142
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:32,930
Lord Lu, you guessed it a long time ago, didn't you? That's why you didn't tell on me?

143
00:15:35,890 --> 00:15:37,900
Who is the sensible emperor to you?

144
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:41,510
The late emperor died of an illness. Prince Huai should've come to the throne.

145
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:43,690
This is the right way.

146
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,530
I understand.

147
00:15:46,530 --> 00:15:48,570
When is His Majesty going to take action?

148
00:15:48,570 --> 00:15:50,830
After rewarding them in the palace.

